radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is enlarged measuring up to 12 mm in diameter with surrounding fat stranding and hyper enhancing walls. The adjacent cecum is mildly edematous. No surrounding fluid collection is seen. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. There is no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys are of normal size with no evidence of stones or hydronephrosis.
